For months now, Corruption Watch has been urging government to put measures in place to curb possible corruption. JOHANNESBURG - Auditor General, Kimi Makwetu is expected to release findings on where the billions in COVID-19 relief funds went. For months now, Corruption Watch has been urging government to put measures in place to curb possible corruption. Funds were meant to assist with food parcels for the needy, a 3-hundered-and-50 rand unemployment fund and PPE procurement. The country has seen a slew of corruption allegations some linked to PPE tenders.